Privacy Policy
Updated and Effective From: March 28, 2023
Association of Surfing Professionals LLC d/b/a World Surf League, its subsidiaries and affiliates and WSL PURE (collectively, “WSL”, “we”, “our” or “us”) understand that your privacy is important to you. This Privacy Policy sets out what data WSL collects from you, including through its online and mobile sites and applications on which it is posted, including www.worldsurfleague.com and our membership management system at wsl.memberpro.net (each, a “WSL Digital Site” and, collectively, the “WSL Digital Sites”) and about you from other sources (for example, at an event or from WSL sponsors or other third parties), and how it is managed, shared or used by or on behalf of WSL. It also explains certain of your rights in respect of your personal data. This Privacy Policy does not apply to information collected from or about our employees in the context of their employment. If you are an athlete or other individual with an agreement with WSL, this Privacy Policy applies to that relationship except to the extent our practices may differ from this Privacy Policy as explained in any other agreements or consents you sign with us.
Here are a few general principles to keep in mind as you read through this Privacy Policy:
If you are located outside of the United States, you should know that the information you provide to us is being transmitted to us and processed in the United States and will be protected subject to this Privacy Policy and United States laws, which may not be as protective as the laws in your country. Also, the WSL Digital Sites place cookies and local shared objects on your computer or device which are further described below.
Advertisements displayed to you on the WSL Digital Sites and elsewhere may be customized to your interests and preferences based on your Personal Data (defined below) collected through the WSL Digital Sites unless you opt out by following the instructions on the
NAI Opt-Out Page
, the
Ad Choices Opt-Out Page
, the
Digital Advertising Alliance of Canada Opt-Out Page
, and
Your Online Choices from the European Interactive Digital Advertising Alliance
. (You may have to opt out using each of your web browsing applications and devices separately.) However, if you opt out, we may still suggest offerings to you on the WSL Digital Sites based on your history at the WSL Digital Sites.
As used in this Privacy Policy, “Personal Data” includes information that can be used to identify you as an individual or allow someone to contact you, as well as information attributed with such information.
You may have the right to opt in or to opt out of certain uses and disclosures of your Personal Data as described below, including in the Opt-Out Rights section.
1. Access by Children
Except as specifically provided in the Notice to Parents section below, this Privacy Policy does not apply to any WSL Digital Sites or areas of any WSL Digital Sites that are directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly solicit, obtain, retain or use any personal information collected from children under the age of 13 years through the WSL Digital Sites in a manner that is inconsistent with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act. Accordingly, children under the age of 13 may be restricted from participating in certain features on the WSL Digital Sites. If WSL is made aware that we have collected Personal Data from a child under 13 years of age in a manner that is inconsistent with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act, WSL will delete this information as soon as possible. For more details on WSL’s policy with respect to children, please see our Notice to Parents section below and our
terms of use
.
2. Personal Data and Other Information We Collect
We collect different categories of information about you (including Personal Data) from different sources, including information you provide and usage information about your visits to the WSL Digital Sites. In some circumstances, WSL collects Personal Data about you from a third-party source, such as streaming or social media platforms or if WSL runs a competition or event in conjunction with a third-party co-promoter and you provide your Personal Data to the third party.
a. Information collected from you
We collect Personal Data you provide to us. For example, we may collect Personal Data provided by you in correspondence (e.g., letter, form, email, or message using a “contact us” or similar feature); through a WSL Digital Site when you create an account, register as a member to receive notifications or to play Fantasy Surfing or conduct a transaction; if you participate in competitions, events, promotions, or gaming portals; if you complete a form, job or membership application, or survey; if you contribute to a public or social forum on the WSL Digital Sites (e.g., comment boards, blogs, social community environments, profile pages, or other forums); or by your giving WSL such information in person. Generally, the type of Personal Data WSL collects from you, and which it may use as set out in this Privacy Policy, may include:
Your full name;
Your sex;
Mailing address;
Telephone number;
Interests;
E-mail address;
Age or date of birth;
Nationality or citizenship;
Social Security number or other government identification numbers;
Financial or payment card information such as credit card or bank details;
Next of kin and their contact information;
Job history and application information;
Transaction history;
Geo-location information;
Unique identifiers such as a username or password, device identifiers and cookies;
Communication preferences;
Interests, hobbies, and demographic information;
Search queries;
Comments and other information posted onto an interactive online forum or included in your communications with us; and
Any other information otherwise described to you at the point of collection or which you (or a parent or other representative acting on your behalf) elect to provide to us.
b. Information collected automatically when you visit a WSL Digital Site
WSL (or its service providers or partners) may also collect certain other information (which may include Personal Data) automatically about your visits or activities when you visit a WSL Digital Site including:
Your Internet Protocol (IP) address which can sometimes also be used to get your general geographic area;
Other unique identifiers such as mobile device identification numbers, domain name of your internet or wireless service provider and type of device used to access a WSL Digital Site;
Browser type and settings and operating system used;
Webpages you visit within the WSL Digital Sites or sites you visited before or after you visit the WSL Digital Sites;
The content or ads you see or click on during your visit and when and for how long you do so, items you download;
The next website or other online property you visit when you leave the WSL Digital Sites, and any search terms you have entered on the WSL Digital Sites or a referral service or website or other online property;
Information collected through cookies, web beacons, pixels, Local Shared Objects and other technologies; and
Standard server log information.
Among other things, this information enables us to generate analytics reports on the usage of the WSL Digital Sites. Other analytic service providers such as Google Analytics provide services which analyze information regarding visits to the WSL Digital Sites. To opt out of your WSL Digital Site usage being included in our Google Analytics reports, please visit the
Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on page
and install the add-on for your browser.
c. Geo-location information
By accessing the WSL Digital Sites from a mobile phone, through a mobile application or another GPS-equipped device, you may be asked to share your precise (GPS level) geo-location information with us. This enables us, among other things, to customize your experience on the WSL Digital Sites or on other sites when we work with a third-party mobile ad platform. In most cases, you are able to turn off precise geo-location data collection through your device at any time through the privacy settings on your device or through the settings in the applicable mobile application.
d. Cookies and Tagging Technology
In common with other website operators, we may deploy, including through our service providers and third party advertising partners, technology called “cookies” and other tracking technologies on the WSL Digital Sites to collect additional information about your visits to the WSL Digital Sites, in order to, among other things, personalize your experience, administer the WSL Digital Sites, analyze trends and user data and gather demographic information. For further details on how we use cookies, and your choices regarding cookies, please refer to the WSL Cookies Policy which you can
read here
. In addition to cookies, these tracking technologies may include the following:
A pixel tag (also known as a “clear GIF” or “web beacon”) is a tiny image – typically just one-pixel – that can be placed on a website page or in our electronic communications to you in order to help us measure the effectiveness of our content by, for example, counting the number of individuals who visit us online or verifying whether you’ve opened one of our emails or seen one of the WSL Digital Sites.
HTML5 (the language some websites are coded in) may be used to store information on your computer or device about your WSL Digital Site usage activities. This information can be retrieved by us to determine how the WSL Digital Sites are being used by our visitors, how they can be improved, and to customize them for our users.
These technologies enable us to assign a unique number or persistent identifier to you, your household or device and relate information about your usage of WSL Digital Sites to other information about you, including your Personal Data. These technologies also enable us to recognize you when you access the WSL Digital Sites using different web browsers and different computers or devices.
3. Use of Information collected
WSL may use the information that it collects from or about you for the following business purposes and functions or as required by law:
to register you with the WSL Digital Site or as a WSL member for participation in WSL events;
to provide you with information about events, promotions, functions, products, services, entries, contests, competitions or other offerings (of ours or of others) that may be of interest to you, and to enable you to register for, purchase or participate in such offerings;
to notify you regarding a WSL event or membership issues;
to respond to requests, questions or comments you have;
to send you newsletters or updates for tours, events, promotions or content that you have previously signed on to receive;
to contact you via email, text message and otherwise about your account on a WSL Digital Site, applications, transactions or relationship with us or an event or competition you registered for;
to process and fulfill your transactions or requests;
to customize and personalize your use of the WSL Digital Sites, and understand information about your preferences;
to enable you to enter contests or events that WSL promotes or conducts;
to track and publish information about your performance in contests or events that WSL promotes, sanctions or conducts;
to identify you on a public list of registered participants in contests or events that WSL promotes, sanctions or conducts or to report participation, results and rankings related to those contests or events and the sport of surfing;
to pay you prize money or other applicable payments;
to assist in administration matters relating to events you may participate in;
to administer all WSL events and tours efficiently;
to contact you for discipline purposes as stipulated in the WSL rulebook;
to contact you for any reason deemed necessary or appropriate, as permitted by law;
to market WSL events, sponsors, promotions and functions and to send you promotional materials or special offers on our behalf or on behalf of our sponsors or marketing partners and their affiliates and other third parties, which may include tailoring ads displayed to you on the WSL Digital Sites and elsewhere to your interests and history with us and on other online properties;
to publish stories, comments, photos or other information posted in any interactive online section of a WSL Digital Site;
to evaluate your suitability to participate in surveys or focus groups for the WSL or a sponsor or partner of the WSL and to invite you to participate in any such survey or focus group;
for assessment, improvement, optimization, research and development purposes related to our business and offerings;
to research, assess performance of and analyze WSL marketing or advertising campaigns on the WSL Digital Sites or otherwise use analytics tools such as but not limited to Google Analytics;
to protect and enforce the rights, property or safety of WSL or others; or
other limited transactional purposes or other purposes disclosed when Personal Data is collected by us.
To perform the above functions, we may match information collected from you through different means or at different times, including Personal Data and usage information, and use such information along with information obtained from other sources (including third parties) and publicly accessible information (such as information available publicly on the internet).
4. Sharing of Information
We may share the information (including Personal Data) we collect from or about you with others for a variety of reasons. In addition to the kinds of information sharing you might expect, such as sharing what you voluntarily post to public areas on the WSL Digital Sites with other users of the WSL Digital Sites, we may share your information (including any of the types listed above), or allow your information to be collected by third parties on the WSL Digital Sites, in the following circumstances:
To identify you on a public list of registered participants in contests or events that WSL promotes, sanctions or conducts or to report participation, results and rankings related to those contests or events and the sport of surfing.
To our affiliates.
To our service providers (who may be third parties) engaged to perform services which may involve the third party handling your Personal Data for the purposes permitted under this Privacy Policy. For example, we use a third-party provider, MailChimp, to deliver our e-mail notifications. We gather statistics around email opening and clicks to help us monitor and improve our e-mail campaigns and as otherwise described in this Privacy Policy. For more information, please see
MailChimp’s privacy notice
. You can unsubscribe from receiving e-mails from us by changing your preferences in the profile section of your account or by clicking the unsubscribe link at the bottom of any of our emails.
If you are an athlete or other participant in our events, information about your registration for or participation in events may be published on the WSL Digital Sites or shared with third party media organizations;
With advertising networks, streaming platforms and/or social media platforms for the purposes of selecting and serving relevant adverts to you via those networks/platforms, and to search engine and analytics providers.
To third parties such as co-sponsors, promoters of WSL events and other third parties, for their own business purposes (including their marketing purposes), unless you instruct us not to by following the instructions in the Opt-Out Rights section below.
To academic, non-profit or similar organizations for research purposes.
In an anonymized, aggregate form with third parties, including our social media, advertising and analytic partners for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy, for example, to improve and personalize your experience on the WSL Digital Sites or to perform analytics.
When third parties such as WSL’s advertisers, sponsors, service providers or streaming or social media platforms, including, but not limited to, Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, Twitch and YouTube receive or gather information about end users of the WSL Digital Sites, including through the use of cookies, pixels, SDKs, web beacons or other tracking software and use that information for targeted advertising.
When we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect the rights or property of WSL or others, protect your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud or respond to a government, judicial or other legal request, or to comply with the law.
In connection with a corporate change or dissolution, including for example a merger, acquisition, reorganization, consolidation, bankruptcy, liquidation, sale of assets or wind down of business.
WSL is responsible only for the content on the WSL Digital Sites and for the use of your Personal Data by WSL. All third parties associated with a WSL Digital Site or with whom WSL may share Personal Data are bound by their own privacy and data collection and protection practices. WSL cannot be held liable for the policies or actions of such third parties. We encourage users to read the privacy policy of any click-thru site they visit through a WSL Digital Site.
5. Opt-Out Rights
You may have the right to opt in or to opt out of certain uses and disclosures of your Personal Data. For example, when you are asked to provide Personal Data on the WSL Digital Sites, you may have the opportunity to elect to, or not to, receive certain messages from us by email. You may opt out of receiving our promotional messages by clicking on an opt-out link within the email you receive or revising your preferences on the "profile" section of your account on the WSL Digital Sites. You may opt out of our sharing your information in the future with third parties for their own business purposes (including their marketing purposes) by emailing us at
support@worldsurfleague.com
and describing your request in reasonable detail.
Please understand that it may take us several days to process any opt-out request and that even if you opt out of receiving promotional correspondence from us or opt out of our sharing with third parties for their own purposes, we may still contact you in connection with your relationship, activities, transactions and communications with us and we may still share your information with third parties to perform services on our behalf.
6. Accuracy, Completeness and Deletion Requests
We encourage you to ensure that your Personal Data in your account is kept accurate and up to date. If you have a membership or account with us and any of the Personal Data in your account is inaccurate, incomplete or out-of-date, please contact WSL immediately using the contact details at the end of this Privacy Policy. You may also be able to access and correct certain of the information in your account by logging into your account and making the necessary edits. We may ask you to verify your identity and to provide other details before we are able to provide you with any information, correct any inaccuracies, or delete any information.
If you are a California resident or are located in the European Union or a similar jurisdiction, you may have certain additional access or deletion rights as described in the applicable jurisdiction-specific section below.
Your rights to access or delete your information are subject to our records retention policies and applicable law.
7. Other people's information which you provide to WSL
If you provide Personal Data to WSL about someone else, such as your child, agent or next of kin, you must ensure that you are entitled to disclose such information to WSL and allow WSL to collect, use and disclose such information for the purposes described above without being required to do anything else under relevant privacy laws (which may include laws of a country they are from or in which they reside). You should take reasonable steps to ensure the individual concerned is aware of the contents of this Privacy Policy as those matters relate to them. You warrant that any information you disclose is true and correct.
8. Security
While we endeavor to protect the security and integrity of sensitive Personal Data collected via the WSL Digital Sites, due to the inherent nature of the internet as an open global communications vehicle, we cannot guarantee that any information, during transmission through the internet or while stored on our system or otherwise in our care, will be absolutely safe from intrusion by others, such as hackers.
If you correspond with us by email, text message, or using web forms like a “contact us” feature on the WSL Digital Sites, you should be aware that your transmission might not be secure. A third party could view the information you send in transit by such means. We will have no liability for disclosure of your information due to errors or unauthorized acts of third parties during or after transmission.
Your account on a WSL Digital Site is password-protected, and you should not divulge your passwords to anyone. You are solely responsible for maintaining the secrecy of your member name, password and other account information, and you shall be responsible for any activity that occurs using your account credentials, whether or not you authorized such activity. Please notify us of any unauthorized use of your password or account or any other breach of security. Any information posted or disclosed on a message board or comment section may be viewed and used by other members of the public. If you post any Personal Data in a publicly accessible area of a WSL Digital Site, you do so at your own risk and WSL accepts no liability for the same.
9. Online and Mobile Advertising: Opting Out
We use third party advertising companies to serve ads when you visit the WSL Digital Sites and other online properties. These companies may use information about your visits to the WSL Digital Sites and other online properties over time, the region of the country or world where your IP address indicates you are located, and other information about you in order to provide advertisements about goods and services of interest to you. These companies may employ cookies, clear GIFs and other tracking technologies to cause relevant ads to be displayed to you. We encourage you to read these businesses’ privacy policies to learn about how they treat your information.
For example, Facebook is an advertising partner and may collect and use data about your online activities to display advertisements on WSL Digital Sites or elsewhere. For more information and to control the Facebook ads you see, visit
https://m.facebook.com/ads/audience_network
.
**If you wish to know more about interest-based advertising, would like to know more about your options or would like to opt-out, you can visit the
Network Advertising Initiative
(“NAI”). NAI is a co-operative of online advertising companies who are committed to responsible practices and consumer protection. You may also visit the
Digital Advertising Alliance
for more information about what you can do if you do not want to receive interest-based advertising.
**European users can opt out from interest-based advertising through the
European Interactive Digital Advertising Alliance
; and users in Canada can opt out using the
Digital Advertising Alliance of Canada
site.
To opt out of interest-based advertising, you may have to opt out using each of your web browsing applications and devices separately. If you opt out, we may still suggest offerings to you on the WSL Digital Sites based on your history at the WSL Digital Sites.
Browser and mobile operating systems also provide other privacy and ad-blocking mechanisms. Some web browsers may transmit “do-not-track” (DNT) signals to the websites with which the user communicates. We encourage you to review the privacy control settings available in your browser or device platforms settings. Note that some of these controls (such as blocking third-party cookies) may affect the storage of your opt-out preferences. To express your privacy preferences for certain companies you may download and use an opt-out application such as
DAA's AppChoices App
.
Because of differences in how web browsers incorporate and activate do-not-track  signals, it is not always clear whether users intend for these signals to be transmitted, or whether they even are aware of them. Certain third parties, such as web analytics companies and third-party ad networks, collect information about your online activities over time and across the WSL Digital Sites and other online properties. These third parties may not change their tracking practices in response to do-not-track settings in your web browser and we may not obligate these parties to do so.
You can stop all future collection of information by a WSL mobile app on your mobile device by uninstalling that WSL mobile app. You may use the standard uninstall processes as may be available as part of your mobile device or via the mobile application marketplace or network. Most operating systems such as iOS for Apple phones, Android for Android devices and Windows for Microsoft devices also provide their own instructions on how to prevent delivery of tailored advertising to your mobile device. Please also review your mobile device’s privacy settings and support materials if you wish to opt out of tailored advertisements.
10. Social Networking
We use several social networking platforms to communicate with you, some of which are operated by third parties, such as Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, Twitch, YouTube and others. This Privacy Policy does not apply to what those third-party platforms do with your information. Those platforms have their own privacy policies, and we encourage you to read them.
You may use third-party social networking services to share information about your experience on the WSL Digital Sites with your friends and followers on those social networking services. These social networking services may be able to collect information about you, including your activity on the WSL Digital Sites. These third-party social networking services also may notify your friends, both on the WSL Digital Sites and on the social networking services themselves, that you are a user of the WSL Digital Sites or about your use of the WSL Digital Sites, in accordance with applicable law and their own privacy policies. If you choose to access or make use of third-party social networking services, we may receive information about you that you have made available to those social networking services, including information about your contacts on those social networking services. Your interactions with those social networking services are governed by the privacy policy of the company providing the relevant service.
The WSL Digital Sites may include features and functionalities that allow you to share information with us that you have already provided to a third-party social networking platform. For example, you may be able to link an account from a social networking service (e.g., Facebook, Google+, Instagram) to your account on the WSL Digital Sites. This may allow you to use your credentials from the other site or service to sign in to certain features on the WSL Digital Sites. If you link your account from a third-party site or service, then Personal Data or other data you have provided to that third party will be made available to us, pursuant to the third party’s terms and conditions, and you consent to our use of that information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. The information we receive from that third party may depend on the privacy settings you have on the third-party service.
11. Links to other Websites
The WSL Digital Sites may contain links to other websites or online services that are operated and maintained by third parties and that are not under WSL’s control or maintained by WSL. Such links do not constitute an endorsement by WSL of those other websites, the content displayed therein, or the persons or entities associated therewith, and we are not responsible for such other websites, content, persons or entities. This Privacy Policy does not apply to those third-party websites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of third-party websites or services visited after leaving the WSL Digital Sites to learn about how your information is treated by others.
12. California Privacy Rights
If you are a California Resident, California law may provide you with additional rights regarding your personal information. To learn more about your California privacy rights, visit our
Privacy Notice for California Residents
.
13. Privacy Rights under European Law and Similar Jurisdictions
If you are a natural person located in the European Union or a jurisdiction with substantially similar privacy laws (such as the United Kingdom) when we collect your Personal Data (a “
Data Subject
”), you have certain rights in addition to those described elsewhere in this policy. This section of the Privacy Policy only applies to Data Subjects.
These rights are in relation to Data Subjects’ Personal Data and include the right to be informed about the collection and use of Data Subjects’ Personal Data, as outlined in this Privacy Policy.
Such rights of a Data Subject also include, where certain conditions are met:
the right to request access to the Personal Data we hold about such Data Subject,
the right to have inaccurate information about such Data Subject amended or updated,
the right to object to processing of Personal Data about such Data Subject,
the right to withdraw consent at any time (where relevant),
the right to have Personal Data about such Data Subject erased or to restrict processing in certain limited situations,
the right to data portability and to request the transmission of Personal Data about such Data Subject to another organization,
the right to object to automated decision making that materially impacts such Data Subject, direct marketing, and processing for research or statistical purposes, and
the right to lodge complaints with applicable data supervisory authorities, in particular in the EU Member State or related jurisdiction of such Data Subject’s habitual residence, place of work or of an alleged infringement of applicable law.
a. Legal Basis for Processing Personal Data
We use the Personal Data of Data Subjects where there is an appropriate lawful basis. Typically this means we will only process such Personal Data where it is necessary (i) for us to perform a contract with such Data Subject or in order to take preparatory steps to enter into a contract, (ii) for compliance with a legal and/or regulatory obligation, or (iii) for our legitimate interests or the legitimate interests of others (including legal, investigatory, personnel, administrative and management purposes) and this does not override such Data Subject’s rights and freedoms.
In rare cases, we may process Personal Data of Data Subjects: (i) for the protection of their interests (or someone else’s interests) or (ii) where it is needed in the public interest. We will only process “special category personal data” where a further condition is also met.
b. Disclosure & Retention of Data Subjects’ Personal Data
We will take reasonably necessary steps to ensure that where Personal Data of Data Subjects is shared with third parties, it is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy and applicable laws.
WSL will endeavor not to keep Personal Data of Data Subjects in a form that allows you to be identified for any longer than is reasonably necessary for achieving the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. We will endeavor not to keep Personal Data in a form that allows a Data Subject to be identified for any longer than is reasonably necessary for achieving the permitted purposes. At the end of the applicable retention period, we may destroy, erase from our systems, or anonymize such Personal Data as part of such efforts. To determine the appropriate retention period for such Personal Data, we consider the amount, nature, and sensitivity of the Personal Data, the potential risk of harm from unauthorized use or disclosure of such Personal Data, the purposes for which we process such Personal Data and whether we can achieve those purposes through other means, and the applicable legal requirements. We reserve the right to keep certain information in our archives that we deem necessary to comply with any legal obligations we may have, resolve disputes and enforce contractual agreements. Our Data Retention & Disposal Policy is available upon request.
c. Storage & Transfer of Data Subjects’ Personal Data
We maintain physical, electronic and procedural safeguards designed to protect Data Subjects’ Personal Data, prevent unlawful or unauthorized processing of personal information, and prevent unauthorized disclosure of, or accidental loss of, or damage to, such information. We restrict access to non-public Personal Data about Data Subjects to those of our employees and agents who need to know the information to enable us to provide services.
We may process personal information in, and transfer Personal Data to, countries that may not guarantee the same level of protection for Personal Data as the country in which Data Subjects reside. Personal Data will also be processed by staff who work for us and operate outside country where Data Subjects reside. This includes staff engaged in, among other things, the provision of administration and support services. All such staff are subject to appropriate confidentiality and security obligations.
We will only transfer Personal Data of Data Subjects to third party service providers if they agree to comply with the physical, electronic and procedural safeguards described above, or if they put in place adequate measures themselves.
d. Data Subject Access Rights
In many cases, Data Subjects can manage their account information, make changes to the information that they have provided WSL or delete their account in the preferences section of the website. If Data Subjects want further details about their personal information held by WSL and how it is used, please make a request using this Request Form.
14. Notice to Parents
The Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act of 1998 and its rules (collectively, “
COPPA
”) require us to inform parents and legal guardians (as used in this Notice to Parents, “parents”) about our practices for collecting personal information from children under the age of 13 in the United States (“
children
”) online and how we use and disclose that information. It also requires us to obtain verifiable consent from a child’s parent for certain collection, use, and disclosure of the child’s personal information. This Notice to Parents is issued by us to notify parents of, among other things:
The types of information we may collect from children online.
How we use that information.
Our practices for disclosing that information.
Certain rights of parents pertaining to personal information of their children.
The operators that collect or maintain information from children through the WSL Digital Sites.
This Notice to Parents only applies to children under the age of 13 in the United States and supplements our Privacy Policy.
Any terms that are defined in COPPA have the same meanings when used in this Notice to Parents (even if defined differently for the rest of our Privacy Policy).
Information We Collect Online from Children
Children can access many parts of the WSL Digital Sites and its content and use many of its features without providing us with personal information. However, some opportunities, content and features are available only to registered users or registered WSL members or require us to collect certain information, including personal information, from them. In addition, we use certain technologies, such as cookies, to automatically collect information from our users (including children) when they visit or use the WSL Digital Sites.
We do not condition a child’s participation in an activity on disclosing more personal information to us than is reasonably necessary for the relevant activity.
Information We Collect Directly from Children
A child (or the parent on the child’s behalf) must provide us with the following information:
To register for a general public account on the WSL Digital Sites: name and email address.
To register as a WSL member at wsl.memberpro.net: name, email address, gender, date of birth, birth country, address, phone number, nation represented and parent name and contact information.  Payment information is also collected from parents in order to process registrations for memberships, events and insurance.
Registration also requires a member name or number and password. We may request additional information from your child that is optional. We indicate whether information is required or optional when we request it.
We may enable users to communicate with others on or through the WSL Digital Sites through chat, email, other social features and posting to public areas of the WSL Digital Sites (“
Social Features
”). The nature of these features allows children to disclose personal information about themselves. We do not monitor or review this content before it is posted, and we do not control the actions of third parties with whom your child shares his or her information. We encourage parents to educate their children about safe internet use and to monitor their children’s use of Social Features.
Automatic Information Collection and Tracking
We use technology to automatically collect information from our users, including children, when they access and navigate through the WSL Digital Sites and use certain of its features. The information we collect through these technologies may include:
One or more persistent identifiers that can be used to recognize a user over time and across different websites and online services.
Information that identifies a device’s location (geolocation information).
We also may combine non-personal information we collect through these technologies with personal information about you or your child that we collect online.
For information about our automatic information collection practices, including how you can opt out of certain information collection, see the other sections of our Privacy Policy, particularly the sections titled “Information collected automatically when you visit a WSL Digital Site”, “Geo-location information”, “Cookies and Tagging Technology” and “Online and Mobile Advertising: Opting Out.”
How We Use Your Child’s Information
We use the personal information we collect from your child for the purposes described in the “Use of Information collected” section of our Privacy Policy above (but note that “you” in that section refers to your child).
Our Practices for Disclosing Children’s Information
We do not knowingly share, sell, rent, or transfer children’s personal information other than as described in this section.  We may share the information (including personal information) we collect from children with others for a variety of reasons as described in the “Sharing of Information” section of our Privacy Policy above (but note that “you” in that section refers to your child).
Accessing and Correcting Your Child’s Personal Information
At any time, you may request to review the child’s personal information maintained by us, require us to correct or delete the personal information, and/or notify us using the email address in the “How to Contact Us” section below to refuse to permit us from further collecting or using the child’s information.
You can review, change, or delete your child’s personal information by:
Logging into your child’s account and visiting his or her account profile page, which will enable you to access certain of the personal information, or
Sending us an email using the contact information below describing your request in reasonable detail. To protect your and your child’s privacy and security, we may require you to take certain steps or provide additional information to verify your identity before we provide any information or make corrections.
Your right to review, change or delete your child’s personal information is subject to our record retention policy and applicable law.
Operators That Collect or Maintain Information from Children
The following operators may collect or maintain personal information from children through the WSL Digital:  WSL and Redesign Technologies Inc (Memberpro). Please direct your inquiries about these operators’ collection, use and disclosure of personal information in relation to WSL Digital Sites to WSL using our contact information in the “How to Contact Us” section below.
How to Contact Us
If you need to contact WSL as directed in the Notice to Parents or if you have an issue or question on this Notice to Parents, you can contact WSL using our contact information in the “How to Contact Us” section below.
15. Changes to this Privacy Policy
WSL reserves the right to update or change our Privacy Policy at any time and we encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically. When we do, we will let you know by posting the changed Privacy Policy on this page with a new “Effective Date.” In some cases (for example, if we significantly expand our use or sharing of your Personal Data), we may also tell you about changes by additional means, such as by sending an email to the email address we have on file for you. Your continued use of the WSL Digital Sites after we post any modifications to the Privacy Policy on this page will constitute your acknowledgment of the modifications and your consent to abide and be bound by the modified Privacy Policy. In some cases, we may request your consent to the changes.
16. How to Contact Us
If you need to contact WSL as directed in a section above or if you have an issue or question on this Privacy Policy, you can contact WSL at:
Association of Surfing Professionals LLC dba World Surf League
149 Bay St,
Santa Monica, CA, 90405
USA
Phone: +1 310 450 1212 or toll free at 1-866-980-1358
Email:
support@worldsurfleague.com
Website:
www.worldsurfleague.com
WSL is best experienced with Javascript! Make sure to enable it in your browser.
